### **III. What Information is *Really Needed*? A Practical Field-by-Field Guide**\
\
| Data Field | Is it Needed? | DPA Considerations & Recommendations |\
| :--- | :--- | :--- |\
| **Full Name** | Often necessary for personalization. | Use only if the purpose requires it. Consider using just First Name for mass emails. |\
| **Email Address** | Core for communication. | Ensure you have a lawful basis (usually consent for marketing). |\
| **Mobile Number** | For SMS/phone contact. | **High sensitivity.** Use only with explicit consent for the channel. Never export "just in case." |\
| **Home/Business Address** | For delivery or location-based offers. | **High sensitivity.** Export only if *absolutely required* for the task (e.g., shipping). Mask/truncate if possible. |\
| **Date of Birth / Age** | For age verification or birthday campaigns. | **Classified as SPI.** Requires **explicit consent**. Strongly consider if this is necessary. Use age *bracket* instead of exact DoB if possible. |\
| **Government IDs (SSS, TIN, Passport#)** | For financial, employment, or high-value verification. | **Highest sensitivity (SPI).** **Never** export for standard marketing or sales activities. Only export if required by law (e.g., financial compliance) with strictest security. |\
| **Purchase History** | For analytics, personalized offers. | Anonymize or aggregate where possible. For personal use, ensure it aligns with customer expectations. |\
| **IP Address, Device ID** | For technical analytics. | Treat as personal data. Often not needed in human-readable exports; keep in system logs. |\
\
**Golden Rule:** When in doubt, **DO NOT EXPORT IT**. Start with the bare minimum.\
\
