\
### **IV. DPO Compliance Checklist for Your Process**\
\
- [ ] **Privacy Notice** is updated and discloses potential internal data processing/transfers.\
- [ ] **Data Mapping & Classification** for the CRM is complete.\
- [ ] **Internal Data Export Policy & Request Form** is established and mandated.\
- [ ] **Security Protocols** (encryption, secure transfer) are technically implemented.\
- [ ] **Audit Logging** for exports is enabled and regularly reviewed.\
- [ ] **Training** is conducted for all CRM users and teams requesting data on data minimization and security.\
- [ ] **Data Sharing Agreements** (for internal significant transfers or external vendors) are in place.\
- [ ] **Retention and Disposal Policy** includes specific rules for exported data files.\
- [ ] **Incident Response Plan** covers scenarios like a lost exported file containing SPI.\
\
By embedding this framework into your operations, you move from being a reactive cost center to a strategic business enabler that builds trust and mitigates significant legal and reputational risks under the Philippine DPA.\
\
**Disclaimer:** This guidance is based on the DPA and NPC issuances. For complex situations or legal interpretations, it is recommended to consult with a privacy law practitioner.}